<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98149107028210></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98149107028210><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98149107028210>RE: Hasted monk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=98149107028210#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 6th 8:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you wish to look at the monk discussion string with Absor you will find that many monks are complaining becuase thier haste items hardly stack with anything ( main arguement involves celestial fists ) Unless they have changed it recently, a senior GM told me that haste items do not stack but rather go off the higest haste available. Now items that have a built in haste spell are different, they do stack with haste items such as the FBSS but do not stack with eachother.  So the best thing to do is find an item that has a high haste bonus and an item that has a high haste spell.  The highest I know for both is the Cloak of Flames (36%) and Celestial Fists (41% spell) for a grand total of 75% haste buff.  Now, lets say you had an FBSS, and lets say for a moment that you are correct and that haste items stack.  Then youd have 96% haste buff? (Celstial Fists 41%+CoF 36%+ FBSS 21%=96%)<br>As you can see this would go over your proposed max for haste.  This is why they made it so that haste items do not stack, because then your delay would be insanly close to zero.  Monkly-Business.com is an excellent site by the way and is very informed, this is just what I have been told by a GM and quite frankly, I am more inclined to believe a GM than an unofficial site until I get all the items and see for myself.<br><br>Just my 2cp<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
