	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Heheh, you said "Tuger Strike".<br><br>Nope, they do not automatically become hotkeyed although it will be listed under the COMBAT button.  Drag and drop the TS button over to a hotkey from there.  <br>And, yes, you can use them with weapons in your hands.<br><br>The only skills which occur as random effects are the defensive ones like "Block", "Dodge", and "Riposte" although random probably isn't an accurate term.  There are numerical values which trigger the skill which include your level in comparison to the target you are attacking, your health, and the type of monster or opponent you are fighting.<br><br>Remember to be patient, young monkey, it will take time to round out these skills to the point where you see a noticable amount of shielding from the damage you would otherwise take, but in the meantime keep working those bad guys!<br><br>--Pusbag Infection <br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
