	   <tr><td colspan=2>lol chimi... for those of us who don't feel like prssing back/forward so many times to match the answers...=P<br>he skills you were talking about will be the same as your druid forage skill, i.e. you will have to asisgn them a hotbutton, and also they will go up in power and efficiency as you go up in skill.<br><br><br>At very low levels my view is this: That mace you are carrying in your primary will help you kill things much faster because of the added damage until lvls 10-15.<br>People may argue but i had a pair of really nice dwarven maces that were a gift to me and eventually my fists outdamaged them, but not until over lvl 20. so... what you will have to do is move the mace back and forth as you fight to keep your hand to hand and 1hb skill as close to maxed as possible. make sure you dont hold any non-weapon in either hand as this will kill your dual weild, which will end up being your highest level skill... so no torches!<br><br>a Desert Madman Hits Maras for 20 points of damage.<br>Maras sits there with autoattack on.<br>a Desert Madman bashes Maras for 25 points of damage.<br>Maras wonders what's goin on. (/em shrug)<br>Maras realizes he his holding that GLS where it autoequipped and takes it off to kill the Madman, just in time to be killed by Cazel in an orchestrated ambush.<br>Maras dies.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maras, middling Monk<br>Tholuxe-paells<br></td></tr>
