<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9812294295259></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9812294295259><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9812294295259>RE: EXP points!!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9812294295259#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1249 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Feb 3rd 7:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.76]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmm.<br>Well, personally I would save them all until you decide to go train in a particular skill.  Then I would burn just one point to learn that skill saving the other four for a skill that is critical later on such as "Feign Death" or "Flying Kick".<br><br>You do not lose any skill points by not training when you level up, but instead accrue these points until the time when you decide to spend them at your guild.  They remain as credits each and every time you go to visit the trainer until you actually train with them.<br><br>Do understand, however, that if you wanted to increase your "Tiger Claw" skill for instance,  but you waited until just before you are able to learn "Dragon Punch", chances are you have maxxed your TC skill out in the field so you will be unable to increase it at the guild.  In other words, you cannot increase your skills past the formula ( skill cap = L + 1 X 5  is the basic equation) that pertains to the particular skill you seek to increase.<br>And yes, there are different formulas for different skills.<br>And no, you cannot use a skill you haven't learned yet at the guild.<br>Hope this helps.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection, whose older monk sister is SO old she had to spend training points in walker usage and crocheting.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
