	   <tr><td colspan=2>In other words, competence.  That one word sums up what makes a good puller.<br><br>I have been acquainted with Gorthin through his posts in the Shammy section for some time now and his answer to the original question is indicative of the quality of thought that goes into his responses to the various concerns of people who need answers.<br><br>I apologize, Gorthin, for over-simplifying all the points that you covered, but I think all monks with any time invested in EQ would agree that a word which provides a cover for everything you said would be "competence".  There is no other class which places a greater premium on the ability to get tasks assigned to them done in a efficient manner than the Monk.  Between the selection of a mob, the process of culling out the individual monster to kill, and then leading it to the slaughter is a maneuver no other class is capable of accomplishing without looking like the inept posers that they are. <br>We ARE the real deal.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection, little brother of Hop Sing, ninja extrordinaire.<br><br>/em Pusbag looks helplessly around for someone to place his arms back in their joints after he dislocated them from patting himself so hard on the back.<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
